Post Description:
As a safe distancing ambassador, Mr Adrian Goh takes on a role similar to that of school prefects - to remind people that their behaviour is being monitored and they cannot flout Covid-19 rules with impunity.

In his job, he has encountered incidents both humorous and unpleasant. Read his story - link in bio @straits_times 

📸: Yong Li Xuan
#Covid19 #safedistancing #StraitsTimes
Comments: My friend who works SDA also got complain said alot still do not follow the rules and yet tried to bully him whenever he is working and had no choice sometimes has to enforce the law. If everyone cooperate would  be better. Obey the rules and do not let Government give them the chance to fine you on the spot and take away your money cos it's not worth it. Overall SDA in here are doing their job. They also human like us trying to meet ends meet

Post Description:
What has 4 wheels and never tires of reminding people to practise safe distancing at parks?
If you guessed the O-R3 autonomous robot, you're a psychic!
PUB's latest "safe distancing ambassador" conducts daily patrols in the mornings and evenings at Bedok Reservoir, when human traffic at the park is the highest.
It is also armed with sensors that can capture, record and process data that can be sent to officers in real time.
Similar robots will be deployed at Pandan and MacRitchie Reservoirs.
Don't be alarmed if you see the O-R3 rumbling around!
Link in bio @straits_times
📸: Jason Quah

3. Operators of venues accessible to the public, such as restaurants and cinemas, are required to ensure separation of at least 1m between patrons
